{
  "name": "Combat Victory Detection: Last Enemy Killed Ends Combat Cleanly",
  "description": "Regression test for Track B fix: when the last enemy is killed, combat ends cleanly with Victory status. The AI turn orchestrator must not loop after combat ends (in-flight guard). Two enemies are present: player kills the first in round 1 via melee attack (Extra Attack chain auto-absorbed). AI goblins use endTurn behavior. Player kills the second enemy in round 2. Verifies combatEnded=true in the kill response and assertState shows Victory — no spurious AI turns after the last kill.",
  "setup": {
    "character": {
      "name": "Gorin",
      "className": "Fighter",
      "level": 5,
